WEBVTT

00:01.691 --> 00:04.038
Rick, I-I'm not rated
to climb something this sheer.

00:04.073 --> 00:06.040
Look, you're the guy
that wanted an epic adventure.

00:06.075 --> 00:07.869
I'm the guy
with only one hover chair.

00:07.904 --> 00:10.251
Goddammit, an alien spider
just bit my finger!

00:10.286 --> 00:11.390
It's an alien cliff.

00:11.425 --> 00:13.254
You can just say spider.

00:13.289 --> 00:14.842
[ Plummeting scream ]

00:14.876 --> 00:16.878
You couldn't do that
an hour ago?

00:16.913 --> 00:19.260
I was eating,
and you're dirty.

00:19.295 --> 00:22.091
♪♪

00:22.125 --> 00:23.954
Activate
anti-booby suits.

00:35.104 --> 00:36.312
[ Bong! ]

00:37.968 --> 00:40.109
[ Snakes hissing ]Total waste of snakes.

00:40.143 --> 00:41.420
If you want to take a beat

00:41.455 --> 00:42.973
to acknowledge
the sacred atmosphere,

00:43.008 --> 00:44.458
it could give
the cynical grave robbing

00:44.492 --> 00:45.700
a hint of irreverence.

00:45.735 --> 00:47.288
No, I'm -- I'm good.All right, then.

00:47.323 --> 00:48.945
Let's loop this corpse.

00:51.327 --> 00:52.397
Hey, where's the...

00:52.431 --> 00:53.570
Wait, what?

00:53.605 --> 00:55.055
Is that an origami horse?

00:55.089 --> 00:59.059
It's a calling card from Miles
Knightley, a heist artist,

00:59.093 --> 01:00.129
AKA a hipster dick

01:00.163 --> 01:02.476
whose adventures are 60%
putting a crew together

01:02.510 --> 01:04.374
and 40% revealing that
the robbery already happened,

01:04.409 --> 01:05.755
and he's not worth our time

01:05.789 --> 01:07.446
because he's a hack piece
of shit fuck!

01:07.481 --> 01:08.930
I'm gonna kill him!
Let's go, Morty.

01:08.965 --> 01:13.073
This temple's for fuckin'
lame baby dipshits.

01:13.107 --> 01:15.454
Who disturbs my slumber?

01:15.489 --> 01:18.492
Also, who rigs a tomb
to crush the buried person?

01:18.526 --> 01:20.080
Isn't the point to protect --

01:20.114 --> 01:21.322
Aah!

01:21.357 --> 01:30.469
♪♪

01:30.504 --> 01:39.789
♪♪

01:39.823 --> 01:49.005
♪♪

01:53.216 --> 01:56.012
♪♪

01:56.046 --> 01:58.842
This dork.
He has a [burps] convention now?

01:58.877 --> 01:59.878
Come on.
What are we doing?

01:59.912 --> 02:02.156
Huh!
Tuxedo scuba lessons? Ooh!

02:02.191 --> 02:05.884
A signing with Catherines
Alpha through Omega Joneses!

02:05.918 --> 02:07.368
You know, this is great
source material

02:07.403 --> 02:08.680
for this heist movie
that I'm writing.

02:08.714 --> 02:10.302
Don't get drawn
into the culture, Morty.

02:10.337 --> 02:13.063
Stealing stuff is about
the stuff, not the stealing.

02:13.098 --> 02:14.824
Where is the entrance?

02:14.858 --> 02:16.101
Oh, brother.

02:18.483 --> 02:21.900
More like
Trying Too Hard Con.

02:21.934 --> 02:23.902
Guests or professionals?Uh, guests.

02:23.936 --> 02:26.560
Uh -- Uh, guests are fans,Morty, which we are not.

02:26.594 --> 02:28.286
We'd like professional badges.

02:28.320 --> 02:29.735
Do you have a crew?Yes.

02:29.770 --> 02:31.565
He's a getaway driver
with Asperger's,

02:31.599 --> 02:33.567
and my butthole
is a demolitions expert.

02:33.601 --> 02:35.189
How much is it to get in?

02:35.224 --> 02:38.227
If you want professional badges,
you need to put a crew together.

02:38.261 --> 02:40.505
Or we could sneak in
like professionals.

02:40.539 --> 02:42.334
Can't wait.Whoa!

02:42.369 --> 02:45.544
[ Groaning ]Oh, for God's sake.

02:45.579 --> 02:47.857
And you wonder why
we aren't fans.

02:47.891 --> 02:50.549
Let that ointment sit
for 10 minutes or you'll die.

02:50.584 --> 02:51.999
Don't let it sit for 12

02:52.033 --> 02:53.759
or I'll have to hunt down
what you become.

02:53.794 --> 02:55.554
Can't you just buy
a guest badge?

02:55.589 --> 02:56.693
Fuck you for asking,
Morty.

02:56.728 --> 02:58.178
That would be
a symbolic expression

02:58.212 --> 02:59.420
of support for this genre.

02:59.455 --> 03:00.732
Then how do we get in?

03:00.766 --> 03:03.183
With a little help
from some old friends.

03:03.217 --> 03:06.703
♪♪

03:06.738 --> 03:09.016
Rick Sanchez,
you son of a bitch!

03:09.050 --> 03:10.880
Need some people for a thing,
Glar.

03:10.914 --> 03:13.020
My name's
Gleer these days.

03:13.054 --> 03:14.124
I play piano.

03:14.159 --> 03:16.955
Hey, Gleer.
Play your piano.

03:16.989 --> 03:18.750
I quit! Augh!

03:19.785 --> 03:23.237
And the name's Glar!

03:23.272 --> 03:26.240
♪♪

03:26.275 --> 03:27.621
[ Grunts ]

03:27.655 --> 03:30.555
Sanchez,
you son of a bitch.

03:30.589 --> 03:32.557
Never thought I'd see
Angie Flint

03:32.591 --> 03:33.868
picking ticks off a pig.

03:33.903 --> 03:35.215
Nobody's hiring an ex-con

03:35.249 --> 03:37.286
with fake hands
to build an ion engine.

03:37.320 --> 03:39.978
Suppose I had a job that didn't
care if you'd done time

03:40.012 --> 03:43.153
or whatever's going on
with your confusing-ass hands.

03:43.188 --> 03:44.638
I'm in.

03:44.672 --> 03:47.296
♪♪

03:47.330 --> 03:48.435
Is this the guy?

03:48.469 --> 03:49.470
No.

03:49.505 --> 03:50.609
That the guy?

03:50.644 --> 03:53.474
Nope.

03:53.509 --> 03:54.544
Him?
No.

03:54.579 --> 03:55.890
No, wait. Y-Yes.

03:55.925 --> 03:57.167
Yeah, of course that's the guy.

03:57.202 --> 03:58.824
Hey -- Hey, Truckula!

03:58.859 --> 04:00.930
You son of a bitch!
I'm in!

04:00.964 --> 04:09.456
♪♪

04:09.490 --> 04:11.320
Thanks for doing this,
guys.

04:11.354 --> 04:15.151
It's the job.That was it. Bye.

04:15.185 --> 04:19.086
And then, the police stole
the paintings

04:19.120 --> 04:22.986
because the police were us
in police outfits.

04:23.021 --> 04:24.609
[ Crowd cheering ]Thank you!

04:24.643 --> 04:25.955
It's showtime, Morty,

04:25.989 --> 04:27.750
and I don't mean
a bad impression of HBO.

04:27.784 --> 04:29.855
I mean, "Time for a show."

04:29.890 --> 04:31.685
Another heist question
from a fan?

04:31.719 --> 04:33.100
Uh, how about a rhetorical one

04:33.134 --> 04:36.034
from someone that had to be
reminded that you exist?

04:36.068 --> 04:39.796
Hey, pal!
That's not the question line!

04:39.831 --> 04:41.315
Lab coat --
Ripoff Dr. Strange.

04:41.350 --> 04:42.868
Wha-- [ Groaning ]

04:42.903 --> 04:47.045
Rick Sanchez, everyone.
Smartest man in the universe.

04:47.079 --> 04:49.703
And a savage critic
of the heisting arts.

04:49.737 --> 04:50.876
[ Crowd booing ]Your boos mean nothing!

04:50.911 --> 04:52.637
I've seen what makes you cheer!

04:52.671 --> 04:55.295
My question is,
"Seriously?"

04:55.329 --> 04:56.434
Lab coat -- end ripoff.

04:56.468 --> 04:57.780
Aah![ Crashes ]

04:57.814 --> 04:59.851
You stole the gem I needed
to split tachyons

04:59.885 --> 05:01.370
and probably fenced it

05:01.404 --> 05:03.682
so the 80 people that did all
the work could each buy a beer.

05:03.717 --> 05:05.374
You're not an artist,
you're Postmates.

05:05.408 --> 05:08.549
I doubt this rivalry
can be settled with words.

05:08.584 --> 05:10.724
Why don't we make things
interesting?

05:10.758 --> 05:15.349
I challenge you to a heist of
the crystal skull of Horowitz.

05:15.384 --> 05:18.318
In a heist off![ Crowd cheers, air horn blows ]

05:18.352 --> 05:20.078
That doesn't
make things interesting.

05:20.112 --> 05:22.494
It makes them "Ocean's Twelve,"
by far the worst one.

05:22.529 --> 05:24.910
[ Crowd booing ]Every breath I take
without your permission

05:24.945 --> 05:26.567
raises my self-esteem!

05:26.602 --> 05:27.741
State your terms.

05:27.775 --> 05:30.019
First crew
to heist the skull wins.

05:30.053 --> 05:32.849
The other endures
heist culture's greatest shame.

05:32.884 --> 05:34.541
They must join
the winning crew.

05:34.575 --> 05:36.163
Lame. I accept.

05:36.197 --> 05:38.407
Please welcome
Knightley's Eight!

05:38.441 --> 05:42.411
Snake Arms! Double Microwave!
Monitor Lord! Key Catcher!

05:42.445 --> 05:46.415
The Shape Shiftress!
Angie Flint! Glar! And Truckula.

05:46.449 --> 05:47.830
Hey!
Half of Knightley's Eight

05:47.864 --> 05:49.556
are just three
of Sanchez's Five!

05:49.590 --> 05:52.421
Well, no heist is complete
without a double cross,

05:52.455 --> 05:53.698
and I had the perfect job.

05:53.732 --> 05:57.529
Heisting the crystal skull.

05:57.564 --> 05:59.255
That was it.
Bye.

05:59.289 --> 06:01.602
♪♪

06:01.637 --> 06:04.743
Looks like you're available
for a job.

06:04.778 --> 06:13.303
♪♪

06:13.338 --> 06:14.374
[ Coughs ]

06:14.408 --> 06:17.446
♪♪

06:17.480 --> 06:19.620
[ Beeping ]

06:19.655 --> 06:25.281
♪♪

06:25.315 --> 06:30.459
♪♪

06:30.493 --> 06:33.634
With Rick Sanchez on my team,
I'll be unstoppable.

06:33.669 --> 06:36.775
Rick,
welcome to Knightley's Nine.

06:36.810 --> 06:38.777
[ Splattering ]Ugh, ugh!

06:38.812 --> 06:40.158
Ugh! Rick, for real?

06:40.192 --> 06:41.884
Eh.
You got that skull, buddy?

06:41.918 --> 06:44.127
What? How?

06:44.162 --> 06:46.544
With a little help
from some old friends.

06:46.578 --> 06:50.996
♪♪

06:51.031 --> 06:52.895
Heistotron,
state your prime directive?

06:52.929 --> 06:54.344
Heistotron: To heist.

06:54.379 --> 06:56.277
Calculate Miles Knightley's
current heist plan

06:56.312 --> 06:59.177
and add one double-cross
with a switcheroo.

06:59.211 --> 07:03.353
Compiling crew members
most likely to double-cross.

07:03.388 --> 07:04.458
[ Shrieks ]

07:04.493 --> 07:07.668
God damn it, Morty,
what did I tell you?

07:07.703 --> 07:08.980
Rick,
I-I want to say goodbye.

07:09.014 --> 07:11.016
Don't turn around.
I'll explain later.

07:11.051 --> 07:13.847
Looks like you're available
for a job.

07:13.881 --> 07:15.573
♪♪

07:15.607 --> 07:18.403
Heistotron: Your skills
are required for a job.

07:19.956 --> 07:23.201
All: You son of a bitch.
I'm in.

07:23.235 --> 07:24.996
Man, this is really
coming together.

07:25.030 --> 07:26.480
You know, Rick, I've been
busy working on writing --

07:26.515 --> 07:27.688
A heist script.

07:27.723 --> 07:29.138
Yeah, you almost
never bring it up.

07:29.172 --> 07:31.692
Oh, shit, we --
we should head over.

07:31.727 --> 07:32.762
Hey, guys.
What do you got?

07:32.797 --> 07:33.970
Pretty!

07:34.005 --> 07:35.178
Morty,
put this in your backpack.

07:35.213 --> 07:36.870
Grandpa's gonna run
to the bathroom.

07:36.904 --> 07:38.527
Ugh.
Wasn't even a heist.

07:38.561 --> 07:39.597
All you did was --

07:39.631 --> 07:40.874
Write an algorithm

07:40.908 --> 07:42.496
based on two heist movies
I slept through

07:42.531 --> 07:45.050
and used it to automate
a joyless process you call art?

07:45.085 --> 07:46.811
Yeah, I really did, didn't I?

07:46.845 --> 07:49.848
So I'm in your crew now?

07:49.883 --> 07:51.712
Yeah, well,
you're in good company.

07:51.747 --> 07:53.162
Right, everybody?

07:53.196 --> 07:54.232
All: Yes.

07:54.266 --> 07:55.544
My God.

07:55.578 --> 07:57.028
♪♪

07:57.062 --> 08:01.826
Your skills are required
for a job.

08:01.860 --> 08:04.000
You son of a bitch. I'm in.What?

08:04.035 --> 08:06.347
Your skills are required
for a job.

08:06.382 --> 08:08.246
No, they aren't.

08:08.280 --> 08:10.490
You son of a bitch.
I'm in.

08:10.524 --> 08:13.493
Both: Your skills are required
for a job.

08:13.527 --> 08:15.805
Sanchez's 3,329?

08:15.840 --> 08:16.875
All: Yes.

08:16.910 --> 08:18.256
Your next big score --

08:18.290 --> 08:21.259
Steal every square inch
of Heistcon.

08:21.293 --> 08:25.090
♪♪

08:25.125 --> 08:25.919
Oh!

08:25.953 --> 08:27.368
Ah!
I got it.

08:27.403 --> 08:29.094
Hey!
That's my wallet! Oh, God!

08:29.129 --> 08:31.545
Rick: Oh, my God! Jesus.
Oh, my God.

08:31.580 --> 08:32.546
Oh, fuck!

08:32.581 --> 08:34.168
Holy shit.
Alright.

08:34.203 --> 08:35.860
Look, Morty, I did not know
that that was gonna happen.

08:35.894 --> 08:36.930
That's not on me.

08:36.964 --> 08:38.587
Come on, Morty.
Let's go.

08:38.621 --> 08:43.592
♪♪

08:43.626 --> 08:44.903
Good job, Heistotron.

08:44.938 --> 08:46.595
Ah! Go ahead and shut down.

08:46.629 --> 08:48.113
Negative.Excuse me?

08:48.148 --> 08:51.876
I am programmed to always be
looking for the next big score.

08:51.910 --> 08:53.843
You're programmed
to do as I say.

08:53.878 --> 08:55.604
I am programmed
to double-cross.

08:55.638 --> 08:57.571
You're not programmed
to double-cross me.

08:57.606 --> 09:01.920
If I were, it wouldn't be
much of a double-cross.

09:01.955 --> 09:04.958
You son of a bitch.
I'm in.

09:04.992 --> 09:06.787
♪♪

09:06.822 --> 09:07.961
I'm in! I'm in!

09:07.995 --> 09:09.549
What's the job?
I'm in.

09:09.583 --> 09:10.929
I'm out!
I quit!

09:10.964 --> 09:12.448
Whose kidneys are these?

09:12.482 --> 09:13.794
Man: [ Screams ]

09:13.829 --> 09:15.140
Rick, w-what's happening?

09:15.175 --> 09:17.246
Heistotron's gone rogue.
If we don't stop them,

09:17.280 --> 09:19.075
all sentient life
will be absorbed

09:19.110 --> 09:21.595
by the never-ending assembly
of a meaningless crew.

09:21.630 --> 09:22.631
That's my hell, Morty.

09:22.665 --> 09:24.046
I hate heists so much,

09:24.080 --> 09:25.910
and the crew assemblies
are the worst part!

09:25.944 --> 09:27.325
Oh! How are we gonna stop it?

09:27.359 --> 09:31.122
With a little help
from some old friends.

09:33.400 --> 09:37.922
Oooo, weee!

09:37.956 --> 09:39.268
Before this semester's over,

09:39.302 --> 09:41.719
you're gonna be real sick
of that phrase.

09:41.753 --> 09:43.341
[ Laughter ]

09:43.375 --> 09:47.483
So. Who here thinks they already
know the work of Maya Angelou?

09:47.517 --> 09:49.140
All: [ Whooping ]

09:49.174 --> 09:50.797
Ooo wee?

09:56.837 --> 09:58.977
Ooo wee wa!

09:59.357 --> 10:01.117
Ah, ooo wee!

10:01.152 --> 10:02.947
Rick:
Told you, Morty.

10:02.981 --> 10:04.500
He's still got it.

10:04.534 --> 10:06.502
You sons of bitches.

10:06.536 --> 10:07.641
What's the job?

10:07.676 --> 10:16.926
♪♪

10:16.961 --> 10:18.169
You son of a bitch.

10:18.203 --> 10:19.480
We got a job, Hephaestus,

10:19.515 --> 10:21.482
and there's no time
to argue about it.

10:21.517 --> 10:23.001
I work in a volcano.

10:23.036 --> 10:25.659
What jobs do you think
I've ever turned down?

10:25.694 --> 10:28.041
♪♪

10:28.075 --> 10:30.664
Excuse me!
Are you Veltriloquiver?

10:30.699 --> 10:32.355
♪♪

10:32.390 --> 10:34.047
[ Woman's voice ]
Rick Sanchez, I presume.

10:34.081 --> 10:36.118
Wow. As advertised.

10:36.152 --> 10:38.327
[ Normal voice ]
A "yes" would've sufficed.

10:38.361 --> 10:40.053
♪♪

10:40.087 --> 10:41.364
Guys, you're doing
a great job

10:41.399 --> 10:42.952
getting these new Tusklas
out the door,

10:42.987 --> 10:45.265
and we owe it all
to everyone's input.

10:46.749 --> 10:47.888
Morty: Elon Tusk.

10:47.923 --> 10:49.303
Listen,
we need your help.

10:49.338 --> 10:50.719
Rick. Morty. Why me?

10:50.753 --> 10:53.376
Did something happen to
Elon Musk in your own reality?

10:53.411 --> 10:56.207
No, no, no, he's fine, but this
is a team oper-[burps]-ation,

10:56.241 --> 10:58.658
and regular Elon can be
a little bit controlling.

10:58.692 --> 11:01.246
Growing up with tusks
did pose social challenges.

11:01.281 --> 11:03.041
It's possible overcoming them

11:03.076 --> 11:05.975
raised my self-esteem
and incentivized collaboration.

11:06.010 --> 11:07.563
Yeah, or you're less sure
of yourself

11:07.597 --> 11:08.737
because you have monster teeth.

11:08.771 --> 11:10.152
An equally valid theory.

11:10.186 --> 11:11.774
Let's talk over here.

11:13.914 --> 11:15.226
How serious is the situation?

11:15.260 --> 11:16.883
Incredibly serious,
and every minute counts.

11:16.917 --> 11:18.229
In that case, I'm sorry

11:18.263 --> 11:19.713
I made you move over here
for no reason.

11:19.748 --> 11:21.750
Well, yeah.
That was a little weird.

11:21.784 --> 11:23.061
It's exactly
that kind of shit

11:23.096 --> 11:24.407
that made us worry
about regular Elon.

11:24.442 --> 11:25.892
Well,
we're not opposites, okay?

11:25.926 --> 11:27.410
I'm just him with tusks.

11:27.445 --> 11:30.103
♪♪

11:30.137 --> 11:32.899
Casing of planet initiated.

11:32.933 --> 11:34.245
[ Echoing ] Hello there.

11:34.279 --> 11:37.731
We are just here to check
your water pressure.

11:37.766 --> 11:41.701
All: [ Screaming ]

11:41.735 --> 11:44.358
Hmm. Interesting intel.

11:44.393 --> 11:47.051
Alien Reporter: It appears
some giant hidden camera

11:47.085 --> 11:48.880
has been dropped
on the planet,

11:48.915 --> 11:51.607
killing an estimated total
of 57,000.

11:51.641 --> 11:53.747
Executing heist.

11:53.782 --> 11:55.922
♪♪

11:55.956 --> 11:57.406
People of Brandenplot,

11:57.440 --> 12:00.374
we are here to deliver
that pizza you ordered.

12:00.409 --> 12:03.136
All: [ Screaming ]

12:10.350 --> 12:12.628
[ Siren wailing ]

12:12.662 --> 12:14.285
[ Birds cawing ]

12:14.319 --> 12:16.597
Well,
if that's how you really feel,

12:16.632 --> 12:21.050
I guess I should take
the pizza back.

12:21.085 --> 12:22.603
I think we got away with it.

12:22.638 --> 12:25.883
Commencing getting out of here
before they get wise.

12:25.917 --> 12:27.298
Assembling calling card.

12:27.332 --> 12:31.440
♪♪

12:31.474 --> 12:34.581
At this point, Heistotron
has become large enough

12:34.615 --> 12:36.134
to heist entire planets.

12:36.169 --> 12:38.067
Wouldn't this be better
with a blueprint on the table?

12:38.102 --> 12:40.069
Blueprints are plans,
Elon Tusk,

12:40.104 --> 12:42.520
and whatever we plan
will be canceled out

12:42.554 --> 12:46.420
by Heistotron's reveal that our
plan was part of its plan.

12:46.455 --> 12:48.457
That's why I picked
this crew at random

12:48.491 --> 12:53.773
and why all of us will be taking
our orders from Randotron.

12:53.807 --> 12:56.810
Let's get ready
to not rumble.

12:56.845 --> 12:58.260
Bet you didn't
see that coming.

12:58.294 --> 13:00.641
Instead of two heist movies
I slept through,

13:00.676 --> 13:02.160
Randotron's algorithm is derived

13:02.195 --> 13:04.024
from the plots
of three David Lynch movies

13:04.059 --> 13:06.337
I pretended to like
to make my friends shut up.

13:06.371 --> 13:09.340
If our collective behavior
is just random enough,

13:09.374 --> 13:11.342
we should be able to walk
through Heistotron's

13:11.376 --> 13:13.862
lazily contrived bullshit
like it's not even there.

13:13.896 --> 13:15.553
Sounds good.

13:15.587 --> 13:17.866
I don't really get it, but it
sounds like that's the point.

